tweet: 13/ Conclusion: Don't give up, because opportunities will keep coming. Find your edge, exploit it as long as possible, keep adapting to evolving landscape, keep improving, keep making money.  Also focus on your mental and physical health, but I won't make this any longer.

tweet: 12/ Even with all of these strategies, the mental aspect is most important. Finding a gem is easy, but good luck holding it for 100x.   Keep learning from your mistakes. When something happens, evaluate what went right and wrong and why it happened.
name: Bobby

tweet: 11/ While I'm saying you should keep adapting and improving, it is important to keep the following in mind. Do what you're good at. Read this advise from the man @GiganticRebirth / @GCRClassic  himself.  Because of this same principle, I was never the biggest NFT guy.  https://t.co/shexnvsZZe

tweet: 10/ EOY 2021 the bull ended and we had to switch to mainly inverse investing. With a lot of sidelined capital, it became clear that people were eager to put that money somewhere. That's when we, next to the continued narrative trading, also started focussing on news trading.
name: Bobby

tweet: 9/ In 2020 DeFi gave us crazy yields. With the retail inflow in 2021, we had to switch up our game again. We had to play shitcoins, memecoins and trade NFT's. It became clear that narratives are way more important than fundamentals.
name: Bobby

tweet: 8/ The point I'm trying to make with these examples should be obvious; as the hurdle of making money shifts, adapt as necessary.  Let's look at some more examples.
name: Bobby

tweet: 7/ In 2021 sales were crowded and launchpads became a thing. The problem switched to: "How do we get into the round?". Solution: starting vc, networking with the right people.  Also just switching up the playstyle, again.
name: Bobby

tweet: 6/ That changed at the start of the last bullrun; allocations became capped. The focus was not only which ICO will give the best ROI, but how can we put more money in the round? Solution: farming KYC.
name: Bobby

tweet: 5/ The crypto landscape keeps evolving, and so should you. Years ago I focused on buying ICO's, as I noticed their upside potential was huge. In the beginning, entering private and public rounds was easy and allocations were uncapped.
name: Bobby

tweet: 4/ Even as many are skeptical, many opportunities will still come in the future, just like they came in the past. All you need to do is find and exploit them.   It is important to stay adaptable. Find your edge and keep improving.
name: Bobby

tweet: 3/ Greed has been the problem in many of these dramatic crypto events; SBF using our funds, people chasing the 20% USTC yield and even Algod buying accounts, lol.  In the end, all you need to make it in the long run and hop on opportunities is capital. Preserve your capital.
name: Bobby

tweet: 2/ First of all, in situations like these controlling your emotions is most important. Many highlighted this the past few days, but unless you have a clear edge, for 99% of the people here it's probably best to never revenge trade and get yourself in even more trouble.
name: Bobby
